scene.message:
Kaneda: What do you want with{nl}
my place? You're not here to{nl}
steal my treasures, are you!{waitkey}{ret}

{color:3}Katsue Kaneda{nl}
A resident of Mikage Town.{nl}
Lately she's suddenly come{nl}
into money, it seems.{color:0}{waitkey}{ret}

Nanjo: Don't be absurd! What{nl}
that old hag calls "treasure"{nl}
is mere junk in my eyes.{waitkey}She plays at collecting{nl}
antiques, but really she just{nl}
buys them up by the wallet.{nl}
Laughable!{waitkey}{ret}

Yukino: That old hag treats{nl}
everyone like a thief, no{nl}
matter who. Not worth{nl}
bothering with.{waitkey}{ret}

Kaneda: Hmph! As if kids like{nl}
you could understand the{nl}
worth of my treasures!{waitkey}Now, off you go!{waitkey}{ret}

Kaneda: What are the police{nl}
doing! I pay more taxes than{nl}
most people!{waitkey}At a time like this, isn't it{nl}
only right they come to me{nl}
first of all?{waitkey}If anything happens to my{nl}
fortune, I'll sue!{waitkey}{ret}

Elly: Everyone pays taxes,{nl}
surely.{waitkey}I don't think there's any{nl}
need to boast about it,{nl}
is there?{waitkey}{ret}

Kaneda: The nerve of this{nl}
stuck-up little girl!{waitkey}Now get off my property{nl}
this instant!{waitkey}{ret}
